The paper deals with the design of succinct data structures for dynamic strings, which involves the use of data structures for efficient rank, select, insert, and delete operations. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the space complexity of the data structures. The design of efficient algorithms for these operations involves the use of combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these data structures to text indexing, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
